<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    {% include "component/head.njk" %} <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style/reset.css"/>
    <title>SQLMan</title>
    <style>
      .content {
        padding: 20px;
        line-height: 1.8;
      }
      .features {
        width: 45%;
      }
      .features ul {
        list-style-type: square;
        padding-left: 20px;
      }
      :root {
        --primary-color: #2563eb;
        --secondary-color: #1e40af;
        --text-color: #1f2937;
        --bg-color: #ffffff;
        --gray-light: #f3f4f6;
      }
      .feature-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
      }
      .feature-card {
        background: var(--gray-light);
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 0.5rem;
      }
      .feature-card h3 {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      @media(max-width: 768px) {
        .nav-links {
          display: none;
        }
        .hero h1 {
          font-size: 3rem;
        }
        section {
          padding: 3rem 5%;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body class="">
    {% include "component/top.njk" %}
    <div class="content main">
      <section id="features">
        <h1>Design Philosophy</h1>
        <div class="feature-grid">
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Small</h3>
            <p>Simple philosophy, easy to understand the whole package quickly</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Transparent</h3>
            <p>No magic behind the scenes, straightforward execution</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Fast</h3>
            <p>Minimal object creation, efficient database operations</p>
          </div>
          <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Restraint</h3>
            <p>Minimal introduction of third-party dependencies, small code size</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <div class="features" style="float:left">
        <br/>
        <h2>Some of the advantages of using SqlMan are:</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Familiar way for you:
            <ul>
              <li>
                <code>sql().input('SELECT * FROM table WHERE id=?', 1).query()</code>
              </li>
              <li>Multiple lines of SQL written in XML</li>
              <li>
                <code>@Insert</code>,
                <code>@Update</code>,
                <code>@Delete</code>,
                <code>@Query</code>
                annotations</li>
              <li>Automatically populate JavaBean properties from ResultSets.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Core philosophy centers around SQL. Enhanced SQL logic, supporting dynamic SQL (IF/ForEach).</li>
          <li>Built-in common CRUD/Paging functionality.</li>
          <li>Offers a rich set of extension features.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="features" style="float:right">
        <br/>
        <h2>SqlMan is NOT:</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>An Object/Relational bridge.</li>
          <li>Does not provide a functional-style chained call.</li>
          <li>A heavyweight framework of any kind.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div style="clear:both;text-align:center">
        <br/>
        <h2>Source Code</h2>
